<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFEA7F0399F7E22DD668FD0E" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFEA7F0399F7E22DD606FE10" blockId="47.[151,1436,229,676]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F0399F7E22DD532FEC6" bold="true" box="[198,544,338,364]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEA7F039B11E22DD5B1FEC6" box="[544,675,338,364]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEA7F039B9FE22DD438FEC6" box="[686,810,338,364]" name="Venezuela" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFEA7F039A56E22DD4DDFEC6" box="[871,975,338,364]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
; likely to be more widespread. It grows on open banks at forest edges or along roadsides, forming mixed colonies with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F039D05E206D3DFFE38" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1076,1229,377,402]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039D05E206D3DFFE38" box="[1076,1229,377,402]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F039C34E206D26DFE38" authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[1285,1407,377,402]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039C34E206D26DFE38" box="[1285,1407,377,402]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFEA7F0399A6E2DFD602FE10" box="[151,272,416,442]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="330.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="60.0">
60– 
<specimenCount id="9D2F89E3FFEA7F0399F2E2DFD602FE10" box="[195,272,416,442]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="generic">600 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFEA7F0399F7E2B9D668FD0E" blockId="47.[151,1436,229,676]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F0399F7E2B9D621FE4A" bold="true" box="[198,307,454,480]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Notes:—</emphasis>
This hybrid between 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F039B05E2B8D5C2FE4A" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[564,720,455,480]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039B05E2B8D5C2FE4A" box="[564,720,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F039A3FE2B8D499FE4A" authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[782,907,455,480]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039A3FE2B8D499FE4A" box="[782,907,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was cytologically studied and described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFEA7F0399A6E292D6DDFDAD" author="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G." box="[151,463,493,519]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="258 - 264" refId="ref31812" refString="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G. (1985) Cytotaxonomic studies of the ferns of Trinidad. Bulletin of the British Museum Natural History Botany 13: 185 - 191, 258 - 264." type="journal article" year="1985">Jermy and Walker (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F039BA0E292D43DFDAC" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[657,815,493,518]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039BA0E292D43DFDAC" box="[657,815,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more rounded and broader bases of the bud scales, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F03981DE16BD6B4FD87" authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[300,422,532,557]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F03981DE16BD6B4FD87" box="[300,422,532,557]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the approximate segments, abaxial segment surfaces scales, and it is different from both these species by having less regularly shaped and darkened scale cells. Many species in the species complex around 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFEA7F03986CE11BD6CAFDD7" authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[349,472,612,637]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F03986CE11BD6CAFDD7" box="[349,472,612,637]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have unequally developed 2 
<superScript id="7C5CEF22FFEA7F039A1AE11ED429FDC5" attach="left" box="[811,827,609,623]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">nd</superScript>
branches, and this pattern is particularly noticeable in 
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFEA7F039984E1F4D661FD0E" box="[181,371,651,676]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. × subremotus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
